    "recap_headline": "Brown University Athletics",
    "recap_text": "PROVIDENCE, R.I. \u2013\nThe Brown baseball team fell by a score of 7-3 to Northeastern in a midweek non-league matchup on Wednesday afternoon at Attanasio Family Field at Murray Stadium.\nThe Brown offense was held to just two hits through the first seven innings, and Northeastern, who entered game leading the CAA in stolen bases, swiped 11 bags on 15 attempts in the game. Senior\nMika Petersen\nhad two hits and an RBI, sophomore\nChristian Butera\nhad an RBI double, and senior\nLogan Meusy\nscored two runs. On the mound, sophomore\nBryan Yang\nallowed just one unearned run over 3.2 innings of relief.\nThe Huskies got on the board quickly in the top of the first with a pair of runs, taking advantage of a walk and hit batter, followed by an RBI ground out and a fielder's choice.\nThe Bears loaded the bases in the third inning with a pair of walks and a hit batsman, but left the bases loaded without scoring.\nBrown took advantage of three Northeastern errors to plate a run in the fourth inning. After a pair of errors, Petersen lined a single the other way into left field to score Meusy from second to cut the deficit to 2-1.\nNortheastern got the run right back in the top of the fifth, taking advantage of a single and pair of throwing errors to get the lead back to two. They grabbed another insurance run in the seventh, putting two on with nobody out before a run scored on a ground ball double play to push it to 4-1.\nThe game opened up in the eighth inning as NU scored two more runs on four hits to take a 6-1 lead. The first run scored on a safety squeeze, and the second came on a single through the right side.\nBrown put up a fight in the eighth inning and pulled within 6-3 with two runs on three hits.\nDJ Dillehay\ndrew a walk, Petersen dropped down a bunt base hit, and Butera followed by lacing a double down the left field line to score both runners.\nNortheastern got a run back in the top of the ninth courtesy of a one-out walk and a sac fly.\nThe Bears will open up Ivy League play this weekend with a three-game series at Yale. First pitch of Saturday's doubleheader is set for 11:30 a.m. from George H.W. Bush '48 Field in West Haven, Conn.\nBROWN UNIVERSITY SPORTS FOUNDATION\nThe Brown University Sports Foundation (BUSF) is the backbone of our athletics program, playing a crucial role in enhancing the student-athlete experience.\u00a0This\u00a0is possible through philanthropic support from our alumni, parents, fans, and friends.\u00a0Your\u00a0gift through the Sports Foundation can immediately impact today's Brown Bears, helping them excel in the classroom, in competition, and, most importantly, in the community. Please click\nhere\nto learn more about how\u00a0you\u00a0can support the Bears.\nFOLLOW US ON SOCIAL\nFor the latest on Brown Athletics, please follow\n@BrownU_Bears\non X and\n@BrownU_Bears\non Instagram. Like\nBrownUBears\non Facebook and subscribe to the\nBrownAthletics\nYouTube channel."
